OL,4,Ccot' to hospital to support grieving
OL,5,Cparents
OL,7,FDavid Ward said: "When we lost
OL,8,FAbigail, we had two or three hours to
OL,9,Fspend with her then we had to say
OL,10,Fgoodbye, which was really difficult.
OL,11,FAnd now, mum and dad can have two,
OL,12,Fthree, four days if they wish. The
OL,13,Fteam at the hospital work with them
OL,14,Fvery closely to allow them to have
OL,15,Fthat time."
OL,17,FJo Ward added: "It gives the families
OL,18,Fan opportunity to create lasting
OL,19,Fmemories. When we lost Abigail, we
OL,20,Fdidn't have that. We had her for a
OL,21,Fvery short time.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G3/8
